{"id": "1446112104309588059", "channel_id": "1446112104309588059", "type": 0, "author_id": "85444984655839232", "author_name": "syrok", "author_bot": false, "content": "Feedback/Suggestion from a new player (on PC) that is loving the game ❤️\n\nIt's mostly **Quality of Life** suggestion:\n\n-Add an option to remove the confirmation from **ultra: annihilation** and **caro: furnace** (or add it to the option that remove confirmation of exalt and posses)\n\n-When you **select a card** ( for example orison, rouse, skills that draw selected cards from the draw pile or even when upgrading a skill) the description of the card always appear and you have to click a second time before being able to confirm or to do anything else, it's really annoying. An option to only show card description if you click a second time on it (or maybe only if you  hold or right click it) would be really nice!!\n(For example right now when selecting a rouse on arc1 it's really really not fluid/smooth, you click on the rouse you want, you click again to remove the description, you click on confirm, and you click again because it show you the rouse description a final time)\n\n-It would be nice if card with **Retain** had something to easily see they stay in hand, something like a special effect, the card being slightly different or an icon to instantly see which card have it\n\n-Same thing for **Fleeting**, something to clearly see the card will be destroyed at end of turn would be cool\n\n-With **Kath's card** it's a bit hard for me to see the difference between a fiamma 1 and fiamma 2 card, more difference between them or something like a little number on top or next to the cost of the card would me nice", "timestamp": "2025-12-04T12:13:13.131000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1446112104309588059", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Feedback/Suggestion from a new player", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
